                                               = audio/music =
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	* `Mod-m`							Launch ncmpcpp, the music player
	* `Mod-./,`						Next/previous track
	* `Mod-shift-.`				Restart track
	* `Mod-shift-,`				Toggle playlist looping
	* `Mod-p`							Toggle pause
	* `Mod-shift-p`				Force pause music player daemon and all mpv videos
	* `Mod-shift-m`				Mute all audio
	* `Mod-=/-`						Increase/decrease volume
	* `Mod-shift-=/-`			Set max/min volume
	* `Mod-alt-=/-`				Increase/decrease music volume
	* `Mod-alt-shift-=/-`	Set max/min music volume
	* `Mod-]/[`						Forward/back track 10 seconds (holding shift moves by one minute)
	* `Mod-/`							Launch music menu, search for single track
	* `Mod-shift-/`				Launch music menu, search for album then title
	* `Mod-ctrl-/`				Launch music menu, jump to song in playlist
	* `Mod-alt-/`					Launch music menu, search for playlist
	* `Mod-ctrl-shift-/`	Launch music menu, search for artist, then album, then title
	%% * `M-F4`							pulsemixer (general audio/volume sink/source control)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                         = windows/tags/workspaces =
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	* `M-space`						Make selected window the master (or switch master with 2nd)
	* `Mod-shift-space`		Make a window float Move and resize with `M-LC/M-RC`
	* `Mod-k/j`						Cycle up/down window stack
	* `Mod-l/h`						Increase/decrease width of master window
	* `Mod-s`							Toggle window "stickyness" (follows you from tag to tag)
	* `M-v`								Focus master
	* `Mod-(number)`
			- Go to (number) tag
	* `Mod-C-(number)`
			- Add tag to current view
	* `Mod-S-(number)`
			- Send window to (number) tag
	* `M-C-S-(number)`
	* `M-tab/backslash`
			- Go to previous tag
	* `M-g/;`							Go to left/right tag
	* `M-S-g/;`						Send window to left/right tag
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                                                = recording =
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
	* `M-PrintScreen`
			- Opens dmenu menu to select kind of
				audio/video recording
	* `M-Delete`
			- Kill any recording started in the above way
	* `M-Shift-c`
			- Toggles a webcam in the bottom right for screencasting.
	* `M-ScrollLock`
			- Toggle screenkey (if installed) to show keypresses
